All three items found. Here's the summary:

## 1. `@RequiresDialectFeature` and `@SkipForDialect` usage conventions

**`@RequiresDialectFeature`** — applied at class or method level to require a dialect capability:

```java
// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/event/service/internal/NewlyInstantiatdCollectionSkipDeleteOrphanTest.java:53
@RequiresDialectFeature(feature = DialectFeatureChecks.SupportsIdentityColumns.class)

// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/sql/exec/op/FollowOnLockingTests.java:55
@RequiresDialectFeature( feature = DialectFeatureChecks.SupportsSelectLocking.class )

// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/columndiscriminator/ColumnDiscrimnatorWithSchemaTest.java:24
@RequiresDialectFeature(feature = SupportSchemaCreation.class)
// Note: sometimes the inner class is statically imported, omitting the DialectFeatureChecks. prefix
```

**`@SkipForDialect`** — applied at class or method level to exclude specific dialects:

```java
// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/sql/partition/PostgresPartitionedTableTest.java:34
@SkipForDialect(dialectClass = SpannerPostgreSQLDialect.class, reason = "Spanner doesn't support PARTITION BY in create table")

// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/lob/LobStringTest.java:103
@SkipForDialect( dialectClass = SpannerPostgreSQLDialect.class, reason = "Spanner doesn't support lo_get function")

// hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/instant/InstantWithNormalizedTest.java:34-35
@SkipForDialect(dialectClass = MySQLDialect.class, reason = "MySQL hangs dropping the table")
@SkipForDialect(dialectClass = TiDBDialect.class, reason = "Values stored in timestamp DDL type columns get the JDBC time zone offset subtracted")
```

## 2. `SupportsArrayComparison` definition

**File:** `hibernate-testing/src/main/java/org/hibernate/testing/orm/junit/DialectFeatureChecks.java:1081-1085`

```java
public static class SupportsArrayComparison implements DialectFeatureCheck {
    public boolean apply(Dialect dialect) {
        return !(dialect instanceof SpannerPostgreSQLDialect || dialect instanceof SpannerDialect);
    }
}
```

## 3. `SupportsJsonTable` definition

**File:** `hibernate-testing/src/main/java/org/hibernate/testing/orm/junit/DialectFeatureChecks.java:1069-1073`

```java
public static class SupportsJsonTable implements DialectFeatureCheck {
    public boolean apply(Dialect dialect) {
        return definesSetReturningFunction( dialect, "json_table" ) && !(dialect instanceof TiDBDialect);
    }
}
```

**Key conventions observed:**
- Feature checks are static inner classes implementing `DialectFeatureCheck` with an `apply(Dialect dialect)` method returning `boolean`.
- Both `@RequiresDialectFeature` (positive gating) and `@SkipForDialect` (negative gating) can be used at class or method level.
- `@SkipForDialect` uses `dialectClass` + optional `reason` string; `@RequiresDialectFeature` uses `feature = DialectFeatureChecks.Xxx.class`.
- The `SupportsJsonTable` feature check **already exists** in the base codebase, so the PR's new usage of `@RequiresDialectFeature( feature = DialectFeatureChecks.SupportsJsonTable.class )` in `JsonArrayUnnestTest.java` references an existing check.
